      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change of less than 2% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. QoI (stiffness, yield force) changed by less than 1.1% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirmed discretization error below 1.5%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms must converge below solver tolerance; energy balance must be satisfied within 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals converged to below 1e-6 for all load steps. Energy balance error remained below 0.05% across the full loading sequence. No divergence or spurious instability was observed."
