      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs used in the validation simulation must be equivalent to those measured or specified in the physical test.",
      "rationale": "Applied displacement rate, fixture geometry, and boundary conditions in the FEA replicated the ASTM F1717 test fixture setup. Torque values for screw-rod locking were matched to the experimentally applied values. Equivalency was confirmed by a dedicated comparison table in the V&V report."
    },
    {
